Multithreading - process of executing multiple threads simultaneously

thread- light weight process,

Thread shares same address space
A thread is light-weight
cost of communication between thread is low
Thread are independent 


Two ways to create a thread - by extend Thread Class by  implementing Runnable interface


Class A extends B implements Runnable

Class MyThread implements Runnable{
    public void run(){
    ....
    ....
    sysout("Thread running ");
  }
  time(int ){

  }
}

Main{
 MyThread t1 = new MyThread();
 t1.start();
 t1.time(int );
}

Lifecycle:
New, Runnable, Waiting, Terminated

Default priority - 5 min - 1 max - 10


start(), run(), sleep(seconds), currentThread(), join(), getPriority(), setPriority(), 
getName(), setName(), getId(), isAlive(), yeild(), notify(), notifyAll(), stop(), destroy(), 

join - join will wait to thread to die(3-> 3,2->2, 1-> 1), yield -> pause the current thread and allow other thread to run  ( 3-> 1,2,3 )

Java 8 
------

Enhanced version released - 2014 


Features of Java 8 : Lambda expression, Functional interface, Method Reference, Streams, Date/Time                    Api, Comparator/Comparable, Optional Class


(a+b)2 ab+ab+cd a+b

public void add(int a, int b){
   int c = a+b;
}

public void (int a, int b){
   int c = a+b;
}

void (int a, int b){
   int c = a+b;
}

void ( a,  b){
    c = a+b;
}

(a,b) -> c = a+b;


Anonymous - without name , anonymous array int [] = {1,2,3,4}

Lambda Expression 
    -> Anonymous function/method
    -> will not have modifiers, data types
    -> will not have return type
    -> {},


Functional Interface
    -> will have "only one Abstract method"(will not have their implementation)
           abstract mymehtod(int a, int b);
      Eg : Runnable Interface - run() , Callable, ActionListner, Comparable -> compareTo()

    @FunctionalInterface
    interface pen{
       public void write();
    }


Method Reference: 
   A method reference is shorthand syntax (::) for a lambda experssion/method that contains just one method to call in general one does not have to pass arguments or create reference to call a method


public Integer getAge(){ return age; }

(args) -> ab.method(output);

Obj :: instancMethod;

System.out :: println(); forEach( Student :: new )

String :: toUpperCase;


StringBuilder s = new StringBuilder();
s.append("""");

.collect( StringBuilder :: new, StringBulider :: append)


